HEADWORD: bimli
<hw>bimli</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a valuable fiber plant (<spn>Hibiscus
cannabinus</spn>) of the East Indies now widespread in
cultivation.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> kenaf, kanaf, deccan hemp, bimli hemp, Indian hemp,
Bombay hemp.</syn>⟦br⟧
